	<td colspan="2" width="100%" valign="top" align="left"><textarea name="desc" rows="10" Cols="55" READONLY>Purpose

The purpose for the formation of the Legion of the Dark Hunters (LDH) is to stand between the innocent and those that would maliciously harm them. Our cause is that of protecting the innocent and good beings of the universe. Our task is a thankless one. No gratitude will be sought after nor is it expected. We fight to keep the night safe from evil, so that the sun may rise again.  

Goals

Our goal is to defeat the darkness and evil that corrupts the land. We try to uphold honor and chivalry where possible and when deemed necessary. However, when it is a choice between honor and protecting the innocent, we will reluctantly forego honor so that a innocent can be saved. What does this mean? It means that sometimes the end must justify the means. We will take whatever action necessary to defeat evil, even if those efforts might be considered less than honorable by others.

Organization

The Legion of the Dark Hunters is based upon a military structure. Rank is acquired through merit and tenure. Offices of Responsibility will be considered a separate entity from the rank and profile of the legion. Each office position will be appointed by election.

Orders
At the top level of the structure for the Legion of the Dark Hunters (LDH) are elite orders. These orders are designed to fine tune its knights to handle specific tasks and goals. All orders are considered separate from one another, but still under the Legion. The only control that is not handled within the order is by the ruling council.   

No more than 40% of the entire legion will belong to the listed orders (10% per order listed). This will reflect the elite status of the group. The count is based upon all ranks from squire up. Increase in legion size will continuously open order positions, as the legion grows in numbers.

The following orders have been established:

Knight of the Steel Pillar - The order of steel Pillar is the Legion’s offensive order. Their purpose is to hunt and track down evil, and if possible eliminate it. The order of steel Pillar is aggressive by nature.  
The Rank in this order is as follows:
¨      Knight commander of Steel Pillar (1 in number)

¨      Knight captain of Steel Pillar (1 in number)

¨      Knight of the third Steel Pillar (20% of the order in number)

¨      Knight of the second Steel Pillar (30% of the order in number)

¨      Knight of the first Steel Pillar(50% of the order in number)

Knight of the Stone Pillar –  The order of the stone pillar is the legion’s protectors. Their pupose is to protect the legion (and its members), and to patrol areas that are influenced by the Legion. This may include town areas and citizens.
The Rank in this order is as follows:
¨      Knight commander of Stone Pillar  (1 in number)

¨      Knight captain of Stone Pillar (1 in number)

¨      Knight of the third Stone Pillar (20% of the order in number)

¨      Knight of the second Stone Pillar (30% of the order in number)

¨      Knight of the first Stone Pillar (50% of the order in number)

 

Knight of the Diamond Pillar– The order of the Diamond Pillar is the legion’s knowledge gatherors. Their purpose is to gain knowledge to help legion members to become better. They are trainers or teachers of sorts. This order also has a second purpose and that is to perform administration duties and to perform recruiting functions.

The Rank in this order is as follows:
¨      Knight commander of Diamond Pillar (1 in number)

¨      Knight captain of Diamond Pillar (1 in number)

¨      Knight of the third Diamond Pillar (20% of the order in number)

¨      Knight of the second Diamond Pillar (30% of the order in number)

¨      Knight of the first Diamond Pillar (50% of the order in number)

Knight of the Black pillar– The order of the Black pillaris the legion’s covert operations order. Their purpose is to gather intelligence information and monitor (without being seen) other guild activities. This order will on occasion handle more subtle tasks that may be taken which are not considered honorable.

The Rank in this order is as follows:
¨      Knight commander of Black Pillar (1 in number)

¨      Knight captain of Black pillar (1 in number)

¨      Knight of the third Black Pillar (20% of the order in number)

¨      Knight of the second Black Pillar (30% of the order in number)

¨      Knight of the first Black Pillar (50% of the order in number)

Ranks
Knight Grand Master – The purpose of the Knight Grand Master is to maintain an overall control of the Legion. The Knight Grand Master may not be loyal to any one order of the legion.

Knight Commander   -  For each order there is one knight commander. They are in charge of the daily operations of their particular order.

Knight Captain – For Each order there will be one knight captain. This position will be a administrative position to the Knight commander. Knight captains will work to perform duties for the knight commander when he is not present. This position does not have any council privileges. Rather it is a position that allows for training to be heir to Knight commander.

Knight of the third rank – For each order their will be no more than 20% of the order with this rank. From this rank promotion to knight commander and Knight captain will be considered. This rank is the upper echelon of the order, and will be considered unit commanders in any battles that occur with multiple Legionaires.

Knight of the second rank- For each order created there shall be no more than 30% of the order with this title.  

Knight of the first rank - For each order created there shall be nor more than 50% of the order with the title of first rank.

Knight  – The knight is someone who has attained a full status in the legion. It is at this time that a member will start considering which order they wish to apply to. A knight will spend time at this rank waiting for a position to be opened in one of the established orders. When one becomes available it will be offered to each Knight errant according to their tenure as at the current rank. If a knight errant foregoes the offered order it will be offered in turn to the next eligible until the spot is taken.

Master at arms – A master at arms is a guild member that is free to due their own bidding, but they are still guild member status. They help when and where they can but are responsible to themselves and to follow all established guild laws. Master at arms are considered full members.
Squire – At the rank of squire each member will be assigned to a knight for training in the ways of Role playing in game. The knight will monitor and vouch for their squire and in return the squire will assist the knight in any tasks that are asked of them (within reason). The purpose of this is to help prepare the squire for future ranks and abilities.
Initiate – The rank of Initiate will be assigned to all prospective guild members. Each initiate will remain at this rank until accepted. At which point they will be raised to squire status.
 

Legion Rules
Ø    Legion members will always converse and perform actions in character. The ultimate purpose of the legion is to provide a place for constant role playing and character interaction. At no time will a legion member talk out of character while in any game.

Ø      Legion members will assist whenever and wherever possible to any other legion members that require assistance. 

Ø      Legion members must stay in constant contact with the Legion itself. This means reading message boards and posting input whenever possible. If a legion member is going to take a leave of absence then an email should be sent to the Knight Grand Master and all Knight commanders (4).

Ø      Legion members will always be on the lookout for new recruits. The basis for recruitment is the ability to role play in character and their willingness to hunt out evil. If a recruit is found they should be referred to the Knight commander and Knight captain of the Diamond pillar. This will allow the Knight commander to start processes for possible acceptance. During this period it is the recruit’s responsibility and task to seek out and obtain a recommendation from 3 Hunters with the rank  Master of Arms or higher. The exceptions being the council. The council cannot recommend anyone to be made squire. This will prevent any conflict of intrest or any claims of specail treatment. 

Ø      Each legion member must have access to AIM (aol instant messanger @ aol.com) and ICQ. Both programs are free of charge to download and use. This is to provide live communication between different members. And for meetings.

§          When in a meeting session the following rules will be followed to prevent chaos.

§          No swearing or vulgarity or threats

§          The most senior member present will be in charge of the room

§          When you wish to speak use three pound signs   ###

§          When you have a question use three question marks   ???

§          It is the responsibility of the most senior member to call upon people in order.

§          When someone is speaking there shall be no interruptions by others and there should be no side bar talking.

§          When speaking make it as brief as possible. It may help to have what you wish to say pre typed in a text box and then cut and paste into the room.

Ø      Hacking of characters in any game will not be tolerated. This is not a hack and slash guild. Therefore power is not everything. Roleplaying is a must. If you are not a Roleplayer then please do not apply to the guild. There should be no OOC (out of charater) comments made in the /say chat command. No one outside the guild should see you speak OOC. It is also recommended that you talk on all chat commands in character but not nessacry.

Ø      Legion members are requested not to join other guilds. If you do, please use different character names not associated with the Legion of Dark Hunters. If in fact you are a member of another guild the council must be notified. This is to prevent in times of war a conflict of intrest. Also if you have an alt char in another guild YOU must keep the two chars seperated. There will be no tolerance for someone posting, upon message boards of complaints against guild players who perform actions with different characters. For example posting that a legion member’s character was killed by another legion member who was using a different character from another guild is unacceptable. Keep in mind that Legion or Dark Hunters might become involved with a war against another guild. If this happens and you are a member of the guild that is at war then characters knowledge must be kept seperated. If it is discovered that legion information that is held as private is being leeked out to other guilds. The legion will immediately remove you from its roster and block membership. Passing of information will not be tolerated in any situation. 

Ø      All Legion council members will have their own message board. Here they will post monthly status for the order and the legion. This will show the members to be active and those that are not active. It is at these message boards only that members will post official requests and complaints to the legion council. Requests and complaints will be posted to the proper message boards.

Ø      The Knight Grand Master, The Knight Commanders, and the Knight Captains will have “Tagging” Privilages to identify legion members. This will be nine different identifiable members.

Ø      Differences between characters will be handled in character and not on message boards. If the difference of opinion is bad enough to warrant council interdiction, then the following actions will be taken

§          Email the council first! A meeting of the council will then take place to determine how searious the charge is. The accuser and acusee might be asked to join in a chat room to discuss the problem. Then discuss any further action.

§          A duel will be arranged between members. No outside interference will be allowed.  

§          Duels will be made by level 1 characters of the same class and race and attributes of the currently existing character. They will each begin with only starting equipment. This will accurately represent the problem associated with each character, while maintatining a balanced chance for victory. 

§          All council members will bear witness to this duel.

§          The winner of the duel will be judged as the one most favorite and will claim rites over this person. Which means an automatic removal if the losing character. The council will also meet to decide whether additional actions need to be taken, such as removal from the guild.    REMEMBER – only the council can declare this duel.

§          The purpose is to offer both members a second chance and to atone for their    

      previous actions. Loser fates are held in the hands of there victors.

Ø      Members that are found to be disruptive to the whole of the legion will be removed from the guild by a vote from the council.

Ø      Council Voting will be handled in the following fashion. Voting points will be assigned to the Knight Grand Master and to each Knight commander. The Knight Grand Master will receive two voting points and each Knight commander will receive one voting point. All votes will be one by majority decision and will be tracked by message boards of the final vote count (If it is necessary or in the interest of the legion). In all situations. Covert actions by the legion will be voted upon and sanctioned by the ruling council. Any covert actions taken with out sanction will be dealt with swiftly. This will not be made public information.

Ø      In the purpose of major decision required by the entire Legion i.e. going to war against a guild. Each member from will be given a vote point based upon the following structure

§          Knight Grand master – 2

§          Knight Commander – Will vote the decision of the order as 1 points

§          All remaining Knights of orders – Will vote with 1 point for each member. This will determine the order’s position and the knight commander will vote that way.

§          Knight – 1/2

§          Master at arms – 1/2

§          Squire – 0

Ø      Promotion is based upon two concepts. Number one is how long they have been a legion member. Number two is based upon what actions they have accomplished and been witnessed by higher legion members. These will be listed below and is standard for all members. Note: it is the responsibility of the member to contact the proper order commander and petition for promotion, using the proper message board.  

§          Knight Grand Master: Elected by all voting legionaires when the position is vacant. The candidates will be the four Knight Commanders of the orders

§          Knight Commanders: Will take this position from Knight Captain when the position is vacant.

§          Knight Captain: Will be picked from that orders Knight of the third rank. The Knight captain will be picked based on tenure in the order and be voted upon by all knights of the second rank and knights of the first rank. Voting will be a majority nomination and one point per knight (third rank Knights do not vote since they are viable candidates).

§          Knight of the third rank Will be selected from the Knight of the second rank based on Seniority and number of positions open (see orders above for number of positisons). In order to assume the title Knight of the Third rank. The candidate must complete a quest TO BE DETERMINED LATER. The quest will be witnessed by two knights of the third rank.

§          Knight of the second rank Will be selected from the Knight of the first rank based on Seniority and number of positions open (see orders above for number of positisons). In order to assume the title Knight of the Second rank. The candidate must complete a quest TO BE DETERMINED LATER. The quest will be witnessed by two knights of the Second rank.

§          Knight of the First rank Will be selected from the Knight based on Seniority and number of positions open (see orders above for number of positisons). At this point a Knight must decide which order they wish to follow. When a position from an order is offered, the knight has the right to refuse it in the hopes of another being offered from a different order. Thus allowing the knight to freely choose which order they wish to belong to. Remember that the number of positions is divided equally between all orders based on the overall size of the legion. If a Knight declines a position, then it is offered to the next in line until the position has a candidate. The candidate must complete a quest TO BE DETERMINED LATER. The quest will be witnessed by two knights of the First rank.

§          Knight will be selected based on service to the legion for not less than one year, and/or accomplishement of exceptional deeds. Knights will be selected from the rank of Master at arms. Master at Arms must complete the requirements of Knight before promotion and they must submit their petition to The Knight commander of the Diamond Pillar’s message Board. Based on the Master’s acheivements the ruling council will vote for the promotion. Note: This promotion is strictly up to the Master at arms and is voluntary. If a master is not promoted then it is ultimately up to their effortst that prevents them from promotion.

§          Master At Arms will be select based on the service to the legion of note less than six months, and the completion of a minor quest. The promotion will be taken from squires who are nominated by their assigned Knight. It is the responsibility of the Knight to post a petition for promotion to the The Knight commander of the Diamond Pillar’s message Board. Based on the Squires acheivements the ruling council will vote for the promotion. However, it is still the responsibility of the squire to make aware to their knight that they are qualified for promotion.

§          Squires will be selected from all initiates that are voted into the legion. Upon a majority vote by the ruling council the initiate will immediately be promoted and a Knight (not of any order) will be picked by the ruling council to start training the squire in combat and roleplaying and the ways of the legion. They will be a team. It is the squires responsibility to do tasks for a knight (i.e.get food or hunt or fish etc).

§          Initiates will be considered for membership into the legion of the Dark Hunters based upon their application to the knight commander of the Diamond Pillar. They will be monitored for acceptance and no more than 3 intitiates will be accepted into the legion a month. This will vary depending on available knights and the overall size of the legion.</textarea></td>
